ğŸ§  Overview

The Spam Mail Detection System is a machine learning web application that classifies incoming SMS or email messages as Spam or Ham (Not Spam) using Natural Language Processing (NLP). It helps prevent users from falling victim to phishing, scams, or unwanted promotions.

ğŸš€ Features

Classifies real-world spam or ham messages accurately

Uses NLP techniques like tokenization and TF-IDF vectorization

Interactive and user-friendly web interface built with Flask

Dataset of 10,000 labeled SMS messages for training

Lightweight, responsive frontend with modern design

ğŸ§© Tech Stack
Component	Technology
Language	Python
Libraries	Scikit-learn, Pandas, NumPy, NLTK
Frontend	HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Backend	Flask
Model	Naive Bayes / Logistic Regression
Dataset	Custom dataset (10k spam & ham messages)
âš™ï¸ How It Works

Data Preprocessing:

Removes punctuation, stopwords, and converts text to lowercase.

Converts text into numerical vectors using TF-IDF.

Model Training:

A supervised ML model is trained to detect spam patterns.

Prediction:

User inputs a message â†’ Model predicts if itâ€™s Spam or Ham.

Deployment:

The model is integrated into a Flask app with a clean UI.

